1. View the last 10 lines of a file
`tail /usr/share/dict/words`

2. Pass `-n` option to limit the number of lines to show
`tail -n 1 /usr/share/dict/words`

3. Pass `-c` option to limit the number of bytes to show
`tail -c 24 /usr/share/dict/words`

4. Pass multiple files to show last 10 lines of multiple files
`tail /usr/share/dict/words /usr/share/dict/french`

To suppress the header line pass the `-q` option.
`tail -q /usr/share/dict/words /usr/share/dict/french`

5. Watch a file for changes `-f`
like checking log files in real-time
`tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log`
`tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log /var/log/nginx/access.log`

6. tail with pipes
`ls -t /etc | tail -n 5`